-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/kia-s-slovak-unit-to-raise-base-wages-4-25-percent-on-average.html
The Slovak unit of  Kia Motors Corp .
will raise base wages by 4.25 percent on average beginning this
month, the company said.  The South Korean carmaker employs more than 3,000 people
at its factory near Zilina, northern  Slovakia . The average
monthly salary of an assembly-line worker employed for all of
2010 was 1,040 euros ($1,400), the Slovak unit said in an e-
mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Radoslav Tomek in Bratislava at 
 rtomek@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net . 